        "160":"In 1989, the $10 million asset test, derived from section 309, applied to both depository and nondepository institutions. <em data-original=\"E-03\">See</em> 54 FR 51356, 51359 (Dec. 15, 1989). Because the 1989 amendments failed to cover as many nondepository institutions as Congress had intended, in 1991, Congress amended the asset test in HMDA section 309 to apply only to depository institutions, and it granted the Board discretion to exempt comparable nondepository institutions. <em data-original=\"E-03\">See</em> Public Law 102-242, section 224 (1991). Pursuant to that authority, the Board added the 100 loan-volume test for nondepository institutions in 1992. <em data-original=\"E-03\">See</em> 57 FR 56963, 56964-65 (Dec. 2, 1992).",
